text: Cathy Parkers (born Catherine Gloria Turner 1955 - 2007) was an Australian water polo player. She competed for the Australian women's national water polo team from 1978 to 1986. She participated at the 1986 World Aquatics Championships. She graduated from Sydney University. == References == Category:1955 births Category:2007 deaths Category:Australian water polo players
